{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433338326,"sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dd07ee001qN9LdnrLoqkwEy","sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","messageID":"msg_ce8dcff50001o3npOY4OnPfwt3","type":"text","text":"Now I see the key difference. In `set-status.ts`, line 56 uses `outputError(fmt, ...)` and it works properly. But look at `archive.ts` more carefully — the current code actually looks like it does handle errors with `outputError`. \n\nWait, I need to look more carefully at the `archive.ts` code. Actually, looking at `archive.ts`, all error paths seem correct already. Let me check whether the `saveFeatures` might be the issue — when archiving, it needs to also handle the case where a task that's being archived is not done/cancelled:\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the archive command flow carefully:\n\n1. Line 48-68: If `opts.featureId` is provided, find the task. If not found → `outputError`. If already archived → `outputMessage`. ✅\n2. Line 64-69: If no featureId, find all done/cancelled tasks ✅\n3. Line 71-74: If nothing to archive → `outputMessage` ✅\n\nBut there's a potential issue: **what if a specific task ID is provided but the task exists and is NOT done/cancelled?** Looking at line 50-63, it finds the task by index, and if found (regardless of status), it archives it. There's no validation that the task should be done or cancelled before archiving when specifying a specific ID.\n\nBut that's not the bug described. The bug description says: `woco tasks archive nonexistent --output json` outputs plain text instead of JSON error.\n\nHmm, looking at the code again, line 60 calls `outputError(fmt, ...)` which should emit JSON. But wait — `outputError` calls `process.exit(1)` and is typed as `never`. The code after it (`return`) is unreachable. That should still work...\n\nLet me actually run the code to see what happens:","time":{"start":1773433338324,"end":1773433338324}}}
