{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773433396175,"sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","part":{"id":"prt_ce8de1bcd001E2Eg00kofx45GQ","sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","messageID":"msg_ce8de129f001kGObXiZPQIO7m0","type":"step-start","snapshot":""}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433410495,"sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","part":{"id":"prt_ce8de1bce001jhY4mID9Z34RHG","sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","messageID":"msg_ce8de129f001kGObXiZPQIO7m0","type":"text","text":"There it is! Lines 951-974 show global error handlers that use `console.error` with plain text. If `loadFeatures` or any other call in `cmdTasksArchive` throws an exception, these handlers catch it and output plain text instead of JSON.\n\nBut the specific scenario described is `woco tasks archive nonexistent --output json`, which should be handled by line 60 of archive.ts. My test above confirmed it works. \n\nLet me think about this more carefully. Maybe the bug was **recently fixed** and this task exists to ensure it stays fixed, or maybe there's a more nuanced issue. Let me look at what `findFeatureById` returns vs what the archive code does:\n\nActually, wait — I notice that the archive command uses `data.tasks.findIndex(...)` directly instead of `findFeatureById`. The `findFeatureById` function is imported but **not used** in the archive code! The issue could be that `findFeatureById` does a recursive search (through subtasks), but the archive code's `findIndex` on `data.tasks` only looks at top-level tasks. However, with the folder-based store, subtasks are flattened to top level, so this might not matter in practice.\n\nBut this is still a potential code quality issue. Let me look again at the `findFeatureById`:\n\n```typescript\nexport function findFeatureById(data: FeaturesFile, id: string): Task | undefined {\n  return findTaskById(data, id, data.archive);\n}\n```\n\nAnd `findTaskById` does recursive search. So if a task ID exists only as a nested subtask (hypothetically), `findIndex` wouldn't find it but `findFeatureById` would.\n\nNow let me focus on the actual task: \"All error paths must go through outputError(fmt, message) so JSON consumers get structured error responses.\"\n\nLooking at the archive.ts code, the only real error path is line 60 which already uses `outputError`. However, there could be error paths for:\n1. What if the task IS found but is in a non-archivable status (like in_progress)?\n2. What if `saveFeatures` throws?\n3. What if `loadFeatures` throws?\n\nLooking at the code, there's no validation for task status when archiving a specific task by ID. This seems like a potential improvement, and any exception from save/load would be caught by the global handler and output as plain text.\n\nLet me wrap the command function in a try/catch that uses `outputError`. Let me also look at what similar patterns exist in other commands:","time":{"start":1773433410494,"end":1773433410494}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773433410511,"sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","part":{"id":"prt_ce8de5303001q90KfZLo5YJ0np","sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","messageID":"msg_ce8de129f001kGObXiZPQIO7m0","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01RBcnMC72ziVb59SG3EdSEU","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-bug-archive-error-json/src/commands/tasks/add.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-bug-archive-error-json/src/commands/tasks/add.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * tasks/add.ts — Add a new task to the tasks file.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage:\n5:  *   woco tasks add <id> --title \"Task Title\" [--description \"...\"]\n6:  *                   [--priority medium] [--difficulty easy] [--effort PT2H]\n7:  *                   [--depends-on \"task1,task2\"]\n8:  */\n9: \n10: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\n11: import {\n12:   loadFeatures,\n13:   saveFeatures,\n14:   createBlankFeature,\n15:   allFeatureIds,\n16:   type Priority,\n17:   type Difficulty,\n18: } from \"../../lib/tasks.js\";\n19: import {\n20:   VALID_PRIORITIES,\n21:   VALID_DIFFICULTIES,\n22: } from \"../../lib/task-schema.js\";\n23: import { outputError, outputMessage, type OutputFormat } from \"../../lib/output.js\";\n24: import { validateEnum } from \"../../lib/validate.js\";\n25: \n26: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n27: // Types\n28: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n29: \n30: export interface TasksAddOptions {\n31:   projectRoot: string;\n32:   config: WomboConfig;\n33:   id: string;\n34:   title: string;\n35:   description?: string;\n36:   priority?: Priority;\n37:   difficulty?: Difficulty;\n38:   effort?: string;\n39:   dependsOn?: string[];\n40:   outputFmt?: OutputFormat;\n41:   dryRun?: boolean;\n42: }\n43: \n44: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n45: // Command\n46: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n47: \n48: export async function cmdTasksAdd(opts: TasksAddOptions): Promise<void> {\n49:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n50:   const fmt = opts.outputFmt ?? \"text\";\n51: \n52:   if (!opts.id) {\n53:     outputError(fmt, \"Usage: woco tasks add <id> --title \\\"Task Title\\\"\");\n54:     return;\n55:   }\n56: \n57:   if (!opts.title) {\n58:     outputError(fmt, \"--title is required when adding a task.\");\n59:     return;\n60:   }\n61: \n62:   // Validate priority and difficulty enums (imported from task-schema.ts)\n63:   if (opts.priority) {\n64:     const pResult = validateEnum(opts.priority, VALID_PRIORITIES, \"--priority\");\n65:     if (!pResult.valid) {\n66:       outputError(fmt, pResult.error!);\n67:       return;\n68:     }\n69:   }\n70: \n71:   if (opts.difficulty) {\n72:     const dResult = validateEnum(opts.difficulty, VALID_DIFFICULTIES, \"--difficulty\");\n73:     if (!dResult.valid) {\n74:       outputError(fmt, dResult.error!);\n75:       return;\n76:     }\n77:   }\n78: \n79:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n80: \n81:   // Check for duplicate ID\n82:   const existingIds = allFeatureIds(data);\n83:   if (existingIds.includes(opts.id)) {\n84:     outputError(fmt, `Task ID \"${opts.id}\" already exists.`);\n85:     return;\n86:   }\n87: \n88:   // Validate depends_on references\n89:   if (opts.dependsOn?.length) {\n90:     for (const dep of opts.dependsOn) {\n91:       if (!existingIds.includes(dep)) {\n92:         outputError(fmt, `Dependency \"${dep}\" does not exist in the tasks file.`);\n93:         return;\n94:       }\n95:     }\n96:   }\n97: \n98:   // Create the feature\n99:   const feature = createBlankFeature(opts.id, opts.title, opts.description ?? \"\", {\n100:     priority: opts.priority,\n101:     difficulty: opts.difficulty,\n102:     effort: opts.effort,\n103:   });\n104: \n105:   // Set dependencies\n106:   if (opts.dependsOn?.length) {\n107:     feature.depends_on = opts.dependsOn;\n108:   }\n109: \n110:   // Dry-run: show what would be added without writing\n111:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n112:     outputMessage(fmt, `[dry-run] Would add task: ${opts.id} — ${opts.title}`, {\n113:       dry_run: true,\n114:       id: feature.id,\n115:       title: feature.title,\n116:       priority: feature.priority,\n117:       difficulty: feature.difficulty,\n118:       effort: feature.effort,\n119:       depends_on: feature.depends_on,\n120:     });\n121:     return;\n122:   }\n123: \n124:   // Append to features list\n125:   data.tasks.push(feature);\n126:   saveFeatures(projectRoot, config, data);\n127: \n128:   outputMessage(fmt, `Added task: ${opts.id} — ${opts.title}`, {\n129:     id: feature.id,\n130:     title: feature.title,\n131:     priority: feature.priority,\n132:     difficulty: feature.difficulty,\n133:     effort: feature.effort,\n134:     depends_on: feature.depends_on,\n135:   });\n136: \n137:   if (fmt === \"text\") {\n138:     console.log(`  priority: ${feature.priority}, difficulty: ${feature.difficulty}, effort: ${feature.effort}`);\n139:     if (feature.depends_on.length > 0) {\n140:       console.log(`  depends on: ${feature.depends_on.join(\", \")}`);\n141:     }\n142:   }\n143: }\n\n(End of file - total 143 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/tasks/add.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * tasks/add.ts — Add a new task to the tasks file.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   woco tasks add <id> --title \"Task Title\" [--description \"...\"]\n *                   [--priority medium] [--difficulty easy] [--effort PT2H]\n *                   [--depends-on \"task1,task2\"]\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\nimport {\n  loadFeatures,\n  saveFeatures,\n  createBlankFeature,\n  allFeatureIds,\n  type Priority,\n  type Difficulty,\n} from \"../../lib/tasks.js\";\nimport {\n  VALID_PRIORITIES,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773433410490,"end":1773433410508}}}}
