{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433421800,"sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","part":{"id":"prt_ce8de5b81001su5pm6v76ORWAQ","sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","messageID":"msg_ce8de53f80016sP8iknySWEamX","type":"text","text":"OK, now I have a clear picture. All the task commands follow the same pattern — they use `outputError` for explicit error paths but none of them have try/catch around `loadFeatures`/`saveFeatures`. If those throw, the global handler catches it with plain `console.error`.\n\nThe bug fix needed is to ensure ALL error paths in `archive.ts` go through `outputError`. This means:\n1. Wrapping the main logic in a try/catch that uses `outputError(fmt, ...)` for unexpected errors\n2. Making sure the `findFeatureById` import is actually used (or removed if not needed)\n\nLet me also think about whether there are code paths that need to validate task status before archiving:\n\n- When archiving a specific task by ID, the current code doesn't check if the task is done/cancelled. This is arguably a feature (force-archive), but could also be a missing validation.\n- Actually, looking at line 63, it just grabs `toArchive = [data.tasks[idx]]` without checking status. This is fine for the flexibility use case.\n\nNow let me create the plan and implement:","time":{"start":1773433421799,"end":1773433421799}}}
