{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433521021,"sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","part":{"id":"prt_ce8dfe5db001rMSt53Ke9Wb2TE","sessionID":"ses_31723c478ffe7uxAauRAAXY9ho","messageID":"msg_ce8dfddd4001ZXWWWwrs8Ru5b1","type":"text","text":"The untracked `.wombo-combo/archive/*.yml` files are from my test run (the archive command moved done tasks into archive files). These are local development artifacts and should not be committed (per AGENTS.md: \"Do not commit user artifacts\").\n\nThe implementation is complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary\n\n**File modified:** `src/commands/tasks/archive.ts`\n\n**Changes made:**\n1. **Wrapped the entire `cmdTasksArchive` function body in a try/catch block** — Any unexpected errors (from `loadFeatures`, `saveFeatures`, filesystem operations, YAML parsing, etc.) are now caught and routed through `outputError(fmt, message)`, ensuring JSON consumers receive structured `{\"error\": \"...\"}` responses instead of plain text stack traces.\n\n2. **Moved `fmt` extraction before the try block** — The output format is determined early so it's available in the catch block for formatting the error response correctly.\n\n3. **Removed unused `findFeatureById` import** — The import was present but never used in the archive command, so it was cleaned up.\n\n**Result:** All error paths in the archive command now go through `outputError(fmt, message)`, guaranteeing that `woco tasks archive nonexistent --output json` outputs `{\"error\":\"Task \\\"nonexistent\\\" not found.\"}` to stderr (JSON format) instead of plain text.","time":{"start":1773433521019,"end":1773433521019}}}
